[[File:Cataract in human eye.png|thumb|A cataract in a human [[eye]]]]
'''Cataracts''' appear in the eyes, they cause short-sightness (myopia), which means you cannot see things in the distance but can see things up close.

If not fixed by a [[Medical doctor|doctor]], some types of cataracts will cause [[blindness]] (which means you cannot see anything at all).

